    "Thus, he made an enormous amount of money and was laughing all the way to the bank.The narrative leads us to the origin of Preventive Law.",
    "The first author (G. Stathis) became aware of the concept through Onassis's lawyer, Tryfon Koutalidis 3 [8].",
    "Koutalidis often provided short legal memoranda to Onassis or others working for him.",
    "Onassis would call for gym time when there were no pressing issues.",
    "During gym time, the businessman, lawyer, and other directors of his business examined hypothetical scenarios to secure themselves from potential risks that could arise."
